summary: An Ordinance appropriating the sum of Seventy-five ($75.) Dollars out of the General Fund of the City of Seattle to pay the claim of W. M. Heenan for personal injuries received by him on the 5th day of October, 1915, at about 7:30 P. M., near the Seattle Sawmill Company's plant in said city, by reason of being thrown from a wagon driven by A. M. Bains, on account of one of the horses of said Bains stepping into a hole in the planking on the bridge on which said Bains was driving, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
